{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"90863030-878d-4996-b4a8-0e7b91b53506","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference modules defined in files listed *above* them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but is listed first.\n\nFixing the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_dQ6UNEFxYVIc9lSPEJmkcx","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Fixing F# file order"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_rhBUgOQtho9c27B7YaQled","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-b3106474699f4e77864111e873782773/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-b3106474699f4e77864111e873782773/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"d72e7ea7-b47f-453d-a393-3d04654cf419","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed *before* them in the `.fsproj`. \n\nCurrently the order is:\n1. `Services.fs` — depends on `Domain.fs` (uses `Order` type)\n2. `Domain.fs` — defines the types\n3. `Program.fs` — depends on both\n\n`Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, which is defined in `Domain.fs`. So `Domain.fs` must come first.\n\nThe correct order should be:\n\n\n1. `Domain.fs`\n2. `Services.fs`\n3. `Program.fs`","outputTokens":450,"requestId":"5C25:229004:61F3A47:6ABCF0C:69F15684"},"id":"b8efb49e-c1d0-4bc7-a8fa-e29a9b8539a3","timestamp":"2026-04-29T00:53:36.996Z","parentId":"14102942-2246-4890-aee5-71ba9da3fe15"}
